## id: magento-downloader-panel
## name: Magento Connect Manager Installer - Detect
## author: hack007x
## severity: info
## tags: magento,exposure,panel,discovery
## description: Magento Connect Manager installer was detected. The software, available via /downloader/ location, requires Magento admin rights and uses the same authorization methods as for backend. If an attacker locates a matching pair of login/password, the installation will be compromised. An attacker can then discover backend URL for login (even if it is customized as described in Securing Magento /admin/) and install a Filesystem extension to obtain full access to all files and finally the database.
## affects: magento
## reference: https://magentary.com/kb/restrict-access-to-magento-downloader/
## reference: https://www.mageplaza.com/kb/how-to-stop-brute-force-attacks-magento.html#solution-3
## shodan-query: http.component:"Magento",cpe:"cpe:2.3:a:magento:magento",http.component:"magento"
## verification: true

GET /downloader/ HTTP/1.1
Host: {{Hostname}}
User-Agent: {{random_ua}}

#@ condition: and
#@ matcher: body contains "Magento Downloader"
#@ matcher: body contains "Log In"
#@ matcher: header["content-type"] contains "text/html"
#@ matcher: status_code == 200
#> extract: name=ex_regex, from=body, regex=/\(Magento Connect Manager ver\. ([0-9.]+)/, group=1





